 IMSGC and WTCCC2, 2011; 
 IMSGC, 2013, 
 2019; 
 GeM-HD Consortium, 2015; 
 van Rheenen 
  et al., 2016
 ; 
 Chang 
  et al., 2017
 ; 
 Jansen 
  et al., 2019
 ; 
 Nalls 
  et al., 2019
 ). GWASs are a tremendous resource for studying molecular pathways and drug targets, and medications with genetic support may be twice as likely to proceed from Phase I to approval (
 Nelson 
  et al., 2015
 ).
